<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="4edd7461-dfac-5595-ac38-0671c708329b" activityNameId="6f227db3-9aac-5c24-89e5-1b460a1fb79e" parentActivityId="06deff8d-b168-53d8-8b19-1fb965c5a3cc" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">treatment of damaged clay material, open dump</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the waste being available at the location (gate) of the uncontrolled disposal. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the waste being disposed, in an uncontrolled manner and waste-specific emissions from open dump are released to air via gas and to water via leachate.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the activity of 'waste disposal of damaged clay material' in an open dump. Recommended use of this dataset: uncontrolled disposal of the waste through dumping.  Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100 % waste clay from material, such as clay roof tile and clay brick . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): H2O na; O 501570; H na; C 1903.3; S na; N na; P na; B na; Cl na; Br na; F na; I na; Ag na; As na; Ba na; Cd na; Co na; Cr na; Cu na; Hg na; Mn na; Mo na; Ni na; Pb na; Sb na; Se na; Sn na; V na; Zn na; Be na; Sc na; Sr na; Ti na; Tl na; W na; Si 352920; Fe 38828; Ca 6109; Al 74399; K 12743; Mg 8012.6; Na 3510. Share of carbon in initial waste that is biogenic 0%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 0%. 0.3513 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Reference for elemental composition of waste:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">ŠVEDA, M. and SOKOLÁŘ, R., 2013. The effect of firing temperature on the irreversible expansion, water absorption and pore structure of a brick body during freeze-thaw cycles. Materials Science, 19(4), pp.465-470.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="9a63625a-358b-4c1d-bf95-50ba038a759b">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0d0e72a0-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">EC</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents an open dump location with mean annual temperature (MAT) of 21.39 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 2274 mm/year, and net infiltration of 1287 mm/year. This infiltration was soft capped from a value of 1338.3 mm/year. The implied surface runoff of water is therefore 51.288 mm/year. The leachate percolating through the landfill has an average residence time of 1.36 years.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Reference for climatic parameters:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">World Bank, 2022. Average precipitation in depth (mm per year), World Bank Group Available at: https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/AG.LND.PRCP.MM?end=2019&amp;start=2019</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">World Bank, 2021. Observed Climatology of Mean-Temperature 1991-2020 Ecuador, Climate Change Knowledge Portal for Development Practisioners and Policy Makers, The World Bank Group Available at: https://climateknowledgeportal.worldbank.org/country/ecuador/climate-data-historical</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">undata, 2020. Actual evapotranspiration, United Nations Statistics Division Available at: http://data.un.org/Data.aspx?d=ENV&amp;f=variableID%3a7</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">World Bank, 2022. Surface area (sq.km), World Bank Group Available at: https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/AG.SRF.TOTL.K2)</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is an inventory for an open, uncontrolled waste dump for municipal solid waste. Ultimate average landfill height is 7 meters. Operation phase duration is 15 years. Percentage of landfill gas directly emitted is 100w%. A Methane Correction Factor (MCF) for landfill air emissions of 0.7057 is employed. Leachate of the landfill is not treated, but emitted untreated. Based on average waste composition and chosen climate data the end of carbonate phase is estimated to be reached 691 years after waste deposition.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2022-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
